B.OU=new A.Q(B.a7,"Why passive voice matters in aviation",'Aviation English relies heavily on the **passive voice**. Maintenance manuals, checklists, and ATC instructions frequently use passive constructions because **the action is more important than who performs it**.\n\nFor example, "The fuel filter must be replaced" is more precise and professional than "You must replace the fuel filter."',null,null,null)
