B.YO={grammar:0,vocabulary:1,reading:2,translation:3,fill_blanks:4,sentence_completion:5}
B.mv={pilot:0,atc:1,cabin_crew:2,student:3}
B.a1Q=new A.T("Modal Verbs & Conditional Structures","Gaps in grammar directly affect clearance readbacks and PIREP accuracy. Focus on shall/must/should and if-clauses in operational contexts.")
B.a20=new A.T("Tense Consistency in Instructions","Inconsistent tense usage causes ambiguity in traffic information. Practice passive voice and future tense in ATC coordination phrases.")
B.a2i=new A.T("Imperative & Modal Structures","Safety announcements require precise imperative and modal grammar. Passengers must receive unambiguous instructions in emergency situations.")
B.a2Q=new A.T("Core Aviation Grammar Patterns","Master modal verbs, passive constructions, and conditional sentences \u2014 the three pillars of ICAO standard aviation English grammar.")
B.XY=new A.bx(B.mv,[B.a1Q,B.a20,B.a2i,B.a2Q],t.dM)
B.a2K=new A.T("METAR/TAF & NOTAMs Terminology","Weather and NOTAM vocabulary is critical for pre-flight planning and in-flight decision making. Build your decoding speed for METAR abbreviations.")
B.a2T=new A.T("SID/STAR & Holding Phraseology","Precise vocabulary for departure and arrival procedures prevents misunderstandings in high-traffic environments. Focus on ICAO Doc 4444 phraseology.")
B.a2N=new A.T("Safety Equipment Terminology","Accurate names for safety equipment and procedures are non-negotiable for ICAO compliance and passenger safety management.")
B.a1X=new A.T("ICAO Core Aviation Vocabulary","Build your foundation with ATC phraseology, aircraft systems vocabulary, and standard ICAO terminology used across all aviation roles.")
B.XZ=new A.bx(B.mv,[B.a2K,B.a2T,B.a2N,B.a1X],t.dM)
B.a2c=new A.T("Operational Document Comprehension","Slow reading of NOTAMs and OFPs under time pressure is a common exam failure point. Practice extracting key data from dense aviation texts in under 90 seconds.")
B.a2b=new A.T("Flight Plan & Strip Reading Speed","ATC strips and flight plan formats contain dense information that must be processed rapidly. Drill reading speed on ICAO flight plan formats.")
B.a3n=new A.T("Safety Procedure Manuals","Understanding company ops manuals and ICAO safety documents in English is required for all cabin crew roles. Focus on procedural language patterns.")
B.a1R=new A.T("Aviation Text Comprehension","ICAO English exams include dense operational texts. Practice reading NOTAMs, METARs, and AIP extracts \u2014 focus on identifying key information quickly.")
B.XX=new A.bx(B.mv,[B.a2c,B.a2b,B.a3n,B.a1R],t.dM)
B.mw={pilot:0,atc:1,student:2,cabin_crew:3}
B.a26=new A.T("Operational Meaning Interpretation","Accurately interpreting the intent of ATC instructions and translating concepts between English and your working language prevents dangerous misunderstandings.")
B.a1W=new A.T("Readback & Clearance Precision","Translation errors in clearance readbacks are a leading cause of runway incursions. Practice precision in both directions without paraphrasing critical values.")
B.a2Z=new A.T("Context-Based Language Transfer","Focus on understanding aviation texts in context rather than word-for-word translation. ICAO language is formulaic \u2014 learn the patterns.")
B.a24=new A.T("Safety Communication Accuracy","Translating safety instructions accurately ensures passenger compliance. Focus on official ICAO safety terminology rather than free translation.")
B.Yg=new A.bx(B.mw,[B.a26,B.a1W,B.a2Z,B.a24],t.dM)
B.a1O=new A.T("Aviation Collocations & Fixed Phrases",'Many ATC communications use fixed collocations (e.g. "cleared for", "report passing"). Recognition of these patterns is tested directly in fill-in-the-blank questions.')
B.a1U=new A.T("Standard Phraseology Patterns","Fill-in-the-blank questions test your knowledge of ICAO Doc 4444 standard phrases. Memorize the exact wording of common clearances and instructions.")
B.a37=new A.T("Aviation Collocation Patterns","Aviation English uses specific word combinations that don't follow general English rules. Study collocations from ICAO training materials systematically.")
B.a2w=new A.T("Safety Announcement Templates","Standard safety announcements follow fixed templates. Master the exact phrasing for each type of announcement \u2014 these appear frequently in fill-blank exams.")
B.Ye=new A.bx(B.mw,[B.a1O,B.a1U,B.a37,B.a2w],t.dM)
B.a1V=new A.T("Discourse Flow in ATC Communication","Understanding how ATC/pilot exchanges are structured helps predict how sentences complete. Study the logical flow of standard communication sequences.")
B.a2I=new A.T("Logical Sequence in Clearances","Clearance sentences follow predictable logical patterns. Practice completing partial clearances to build speed and accuracy on this question type.")
B.a22=new A.T("Aviation Sentence Structure","Aviation English sentences follow specific structural patterns. Study how information is sequenced in ICAO communications \u2014 what comes first, second, third.")
B.a2W=new A.T("Procedural Language Completion","Safety and service procedure sentences follow predictable structures. Practice with official cabin crew communication scripts to internalize the patterns.")
B.Yf=new A.bx(B.mw,[B.a1V,B.a2I,B.a22,B.a2W],t.dM)
B.Yd=new A.bx(B.YO,[B.XY,B.XZ,B.XX,B.Yg,B.Ye,B.Yf],A.ac("bx<i,aE<i,+(i,i)>>"))
